Provisions the single-node K3s cluster (EC2 c5.4xlarge) used by the
k8s-autoscaling guide's benchmark. See ../k8s-autoscaling.md for the guide
this cluster is meant to reproduce.

Prerequisites
--------------
- Terraform >= 1.0
- An AWS account/credentials with permission to create EC2 instances, key
  pairs, and security groups in the default VPC of the target region
- An SSH key pair to access the instance:

    ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -f ~/.ssh/vector_tests -N ""

Usage
-----
1. From this directory, initialize Terraform:

    terraform init

2. Apply, supplying `my_cidr` (the only variable with no default):

    terraform apply \
      -var="my_cidr=$(curl -s https://checkip.amazonaws.com)/32"

   This creates the key pair, security group, and EC2 instance, installs
   K3s/Helm/grpcurl via user-data, and fetches a kubeconfig once K3s is
   active — written to ./kubeconfig (gitignored). Resources are named
   "vector-perf" by default; if you're sharing an AWS account with another
   concurrent reproduction, also pass `-var="cluster_suffix=<your-username>"`
   to avoid name collisions.

3. Use the generated kubeconfig with kubectl/helm and with
   ../scripts/run-experiment.sh:

    export KUBECONFIG=$(terraform output -raw kubeconfig_path)
    kubectl get nodes

4. When finished, tear the cluster down (pass the same `-var` flags you
   applied with):

    terraform destroy \
      -var="my_cidr=$(curl -s https://checkip.amazonaws.com)/32"

Variables
---------
See variables.tf for the full list and defaults. Notably:
- `my_cidr`   — required; CIDR allowed to reach SSH (22) and the K3s API
                (6443) on the instance, e.g. your own IP as a /32.
- `cluster_suffix` — optional; appended to the default "vector-perf"
                resource names (key pair, security group) if set. Only
                needed to avoid collisions with another concurrent
                reproduction in the same account.
- `ssh_public_key_path` / `ssh_private_key_path` — default to
  ~/.ssh/vector_tests(.pub); point these at your own key pair if different.
